==English==

===Pronunciation===
*{{audio|en-us-mooch.ogg|Audio (US)}}
*:Rhymes: [[Rhymes:English:-uːtʃ|-uːtʃ]]

===Verb===
{{en-verb|mooch|es}}

Verb

to mooch (intransitive or transitive)

   1. to wander around aimlessly
   2. to beg, cadge or sponge (things); to exploit or take advantage of others for personal gain
   3. to sap information off of others

e.g., Bret mooched off Terry for the upcoming Social Studies Test

===Noun===
{{en-noun|es}}

moochment

   1. the act of mooching

e.g., "Jonathan!" Bret exclaimed. "Moochment is outlawed at school!"


moochery

   1. A person, place, or thing, from which one mooches off of

e.g., In our case, Nick was the moochery, for he told Mark about the Science exam.

moochist

   1. A repeated offender of moochment

   1. One who mooches; all definitions apply

